# Module 1 QC gate (non-negotiable)

Source: `data/research/course/module_01_read_before_anything.md`  
Enforcement: `shorts_bot/tiktok_shop/module1_qc.py`

## Rule

**Zero Module 1 violations** before enqueue or post. No owner override for “just this once” unless owner explicitly accepts account risk in chat.

## When to apply

- Before `factory_cli enqueue` or `post`
- After Kling render, edit, or caption change
- When owner asks if a clip is “ready” or “GOOD”

## CEO / QC runner

```bash
python3 -m shorts_bot.tiktok_shop.factory_cli qc \
  --video PATH --product "NAME" --caption "..." --account affiliate_main
```

Delegate **`module1-qc-runner`** for batch checks — still **block upload** on any fail.

## Caption hard bans (Module 7 + TikTok Shop Content Policy)

Never ship captions/descriptions with sale/price/discount language, giveaways, off-platform redirects (URL, email, phone, @handle), gambling/chance language, exaggerated health claims, or weight-loss sole claims.

Full defense brief: `data/research/course/TIKTOK_SHOP_CONTENT_POLICY.md`  
Code: `shorts_bot/tiktok_shop/tos_policy.py` + `BANNED_CAPTION_PHRASES` in `module1_qc.py`

## Video prompt / Kling (Module 5)

Banned in generated video: moving water/fire/steam, humans/pets, **phone screens / app UI**, **third-party brand logos** (only advertised product brand), levitating product, static-only camera, listing-matching environment, supplement boxes, etc.  
**Do not freestyle prompts** — use **`product-video-prompt-builder`** (`PROMPT_BUILDER.md`).

## On QC fail

1. Log violation list for owner (plain English)
2. Regen prompt or edit — do **not** lower standards to hit 8–10/day
3. Re-run QC until pass

## Tests

Touching QC logic → `python3 -m pytest tests/ -q` (include scout/QC tests).

